What are Green Thumbz Garden Pegs used for? Green Thumbz Garden Pegs are designed to securely anchor garden membranes, landscaping fabric, netting, artificial grass, tents, and more, ensuring they stay in place. Do garden pegs work in all soil types? Garden pegs are designed to work in various soil types, including clay, sand, loam, or rocky soil. However, soil condition and moisture levels may affect installation ease. How do I install these pegs? Simply insert the pegs into the ground at the desired location, ensuring they are firmly anchored and providing secure support for the materials they're holding in place. Can galvanized metal pegs be reused? Yes, galvanized metal pegs can be reused multiple times. Simply remove them from the soil, clean off any debris, and store them in a dry place for future use. Are garden pegs safe for use around plants? Yes, garden pegs are safe for use around plants. They provide a secure anchoring method without causing damage to plant roots or stems.
